title: Article Rendering Regression
story: dungeo
author: Sharpee Team
description: |
  Locks in ADR-158: stdlib actions emit EntityInfo in message params so the
  formatter chain (`{the:cap:item}`, etc.) can choose the correct article
  per nounType / properName / IdentityTrait.article.

  The original bug (rendered "white house is fixed in place." with no
  article) was caused by stdlib's taking action passing `noun.name` (a
  bare string) where the formatter expected EntityInfo. Phase 2 of the
  lang-articles migration migrates the taking action and its templates;
  this transcript is the regression sentinel.

  See:
    - ADR-158 Entity-Valued Message Params Carry EntityInfo
    - docs/work/lang-articles/plan-20260424-the-cap-migration.md
    - Original bug report: text "white house is fixed in place." in
      Dungeo's web client

---

# Start: West of House. The white house is scenery declared with
# article: 'the' on its IdentityTrait (see stories/dungeo/src/regions/white-house.ts:353).
> look
[OK: contains "West of House"]
[OK: contains "white house"]

# THE REGRESSION: TAKE on the white house must include the article.
# Pre-ADR-158: rendered "white house is fixed in place." (bug)
# Post-ADR-158: renders "The white house is fixed in place."
#
# The positive `contains "The white house is fixed in place."` is the
# regression sentinel: if a future change drops the article back to
# "white house is fixed in place." this assertion text won't be found.
> take white house
[OK: contains "The white house is fixed in place."]

# Sanity: same pattern via alias. "house" is an alias for white house
# (see stories/dungeo/src/regions/white-house.ts).
> take house
[OK: contains "The white house is fixed in place."]
